<h4 class="subsubsection"> 3.1.4.4 Recording and Playback Commands </h4>

<p>This allows demos to be recorded.
</p>
<dl compact="compact">
<dt> <code>record</code></dt>
<dd><p>Start/stop recording camera movement.  If you have a previous recording in
memory then a the new camera movements will be appended.
</p>
</dd>
<dt> <code>play</code></dt>
<dd><p>Play current recording.  The play command also exists in other forms concerned
with performance statistics, not a recording of motion.
</p>
</dd>
<dt> <code>clrrec</code></dt>
<dd><p>Clear current recording.
</p>
</dd>
<dt> <code>saverec file</code></dt>
<dd><p>Save recording as <tt>&lsquo;/tmp/file.rec&rsquo;</tt>, default <tt>&lsquo;/tmp/record&rsquo;</tt>.  It is
only sensible play back a recording in the same or nearly identical map.
</p>
</dd>
<dt> <code>loadrec file</code></dt>
<dd><p>Load recording from <tt>&lsquo;/tmp/file.rec&rsquo;</tt>, default <tt>&lsquo;/tmp/record&rsquo;</tt>.
</p>
</dd>
<dt> <code>recsubperf str - record subperformance</code></dt>
<dd><p>Once a recording has begun this command is used to record the statistics of a
subsection of the demo and is reported as such in the output <tt>&lsquo;file.rps&rsquo;</tt>
when played back.  To finish the subsection call the command again without an
argument.  <samp>&lsquo;recsubperf&rsquo;</samp> stands for record subsection performance.
</p></dd>
</dl>

